						               													<description>First Down Derby is the new interactive board game invented and intended to provide family and group entertainment while viewing or listening to any football game played at any level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First Down Derby includes a 23&amp;quot;x11&amp;quot; Game Board including Rules of the Game, 1,000 Derby Dollars, 10 numbered multicolored markers and 10 First Down Derby Champion Stickers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Up to ten people may play at one time, but all players must start and finish at the same time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First Down Derby play may start or end at any time during the duration of any football game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) In the beginning of the game a banker is elected. The banker should also play the game. The banker is responsible for distributing the Derby Dollars to all players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2) Each player then picks a marker, numbered 1-10.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3) Before the start of each series of offensive downs, each player must place his/her marker on the position they feel the offensive team will obtain a first down, no first down or a turn-over (fumble or interception).  More than one player may place their marker on a position at one time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
